Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a light brown-grey pottery vessel, the fabric contains many small white inclusions, the exterior is covered with a light-brown slip and very faint traces of a number of lines of black-painted hieratic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (394006) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/394006)
